<p><b>Q. How is DebtFriends different from other “debt settlement” companies who promise to negotiate deals for you for a fee?</b></p>

<p>A. DebtFriends is free online software that lets you negotiate deals directly with your lender. No middle man. You never pay a fee, the lender always pays. You are always in control. There are no recurring fees or trial periods you might forget about - it’s simply free to use.</p>
<p>
In addition, DebtFriends is a marketplace where lenders compete for your “wallet share”. What that means is that because you may not be able to pay all of your debt off at once, lenders will lower the amount they are willing to settle for in the hopes that you will negotiate with them first. It’s a win/win.</p>
<p>
In contrast, debt settlement companies negotiate with the lenders on your behalf. They act as the middle man between you and your lender. You sign up with them and commit to a large fee for their service without ever knowing if it’s going to work or whether you’ll be able to afford it. They typically recommend you go delinquent on your good debt which can have negative consequences on your credit and can actually get you further into debt with late fees and penalties. They hide how they are negotiating with the lenders because they don’t want you to know that you can do it yourself. This is silly. It’s your money, you should be able to control how you negotiate. 
</p>
